function pointer

1) 	Declaration: 
	
	(pointers to regular functions vs member functions)

	static AForm* (*fptr[])(std::string target);
	Array of pointers to regular functions that return AForm* and take a std::string parameter.

	static AForm* (Intern::*fptr[])(std::string target);
	Array of pointers to member functions that return AForm* and take a std::string parameter.

	Function pointer declaration explained.

	static AForm* (Intern::*fptr[])(std::string target);
                    --   a   --   --  b --   -- c  --            - -  d ---

	a) Return type of the function pointer
	b) Member function. Without that, it means a regular function
	c) * means a pointer , [] means an array of pointers
	d) () determines that this is a function, without () it would mean it is a variable

